## Persona 2: Dr. Marcus Williams - Clinical Manager

![Clinical Manager](https://via.placeholder.com/150x150/22C55E/FFFFFF?text=MW)

### Demographics
- **Age:** 38
- **Role:** Emergency Department Clinical Manager
- **Experience:** 12 years clinical practice, 3 years in management
- **Technical Proficiency:** Advanced (uses multiple clinical systems, comfortable with data tools)
- **Location:** Busy urban ED, 500+ monthly visits

### Goals
1. **Optimize patient flow** through the ED (reduce wait times, improve throughput)
2. **Monitor staff workload** and prevent burnout
3. **Track quality metrics** (patient satisfaction, door-to-doctor time, readmission rates)
4. **Make real-time staffing decisions** based on current patient volume

### Pain Points
- Current EMR dashboard is **slow and not designed for real-time monitoring**
- Cannot see granular data by shift or provider
- Needs IT support to generate custom reports
- Misses critical trends because data is only available at end of day

### Motivations
- Deliver excellent patient care efficiently
- Support and protect clinical team from overwork
- Use data to advocate for additional resources when needed

### Technology Usage
- **Devices:** Desktop at workstation (50%), Mobile phone (30%), Tablet during rounds (20%)
- **Peak Usage Times:** Throughout shift (6 AM - 6 PM), on-call evenings
- **Preferred Features:** Real-time updates, drill-down by provider/shift, mobile access

### Key User Scenarios
1. **Shift Handoff:** Reviews past 8 hours before briefing incoming team
2. **Mid-Shift Check:** Monitors current ED census, bed requests, and average wait time
3. **Quality Review:** Analyzes monthly trends to identify improvement opportunities

