## Persona 3: Emily Rodriguez - Data Analyst

![Data Analyst](https://via.placeholder.com/150x150/F59E0B/FFFFFF?text=ER)

### Demographics
- **Age:** 29
- **Role:** Healthcare Data Analyst, Hospital Analytics Department
- **Experience:** 5 years in healthcare analytics
- **Technical Proficiency:** Expert (Python, R, SQL, Tableau, Power BI)
- **Location:** Corporate analytics office, supports multiple facilities

### Goals
1. **Perform deep-dive analysis** on operational and clinical data
2. **Build predictive models** for patient admissions, readmissions, and resource needs
3. **Export clean datasets** for statistical analysis and modeling
4. **Create custom visualizations** for stakeholder presentations

### Pain Points
- Current systems only provide **pre-built reports** with limited customization
- Data export is manual and time-consuming (CSV downloads, data cleaning)
- Cannot access raw data directly without contacting IT
- Lacks API access for automation and integration with analytical tools

### Motivations
- Uncover actionable insights that improve patient care and efficiency
- Build reputation as strategic partner to clinical and operational leaders
- Automate repetitive tasks to focus on high-value analysis

### Technology Usage
- **Devices:** Desktop workstation (95%), Laptop (5%)
- **Peak Usage Times:** 9 AM - 5 PM (standard business hours)
- **Preferred Features:** API access, advanced filters, SQL/Python integration, bulk exports

### Key User Scenarios
1. **Quarterly Analysis:** Pulls 3 months of data to identify seasonal trends
2. **Ad-Hoc Requests:** Executive asks for specific metric breakdown by department and time period
3. **Model Development:** Exports historical data to build admission forecasting model

---

## Summary: Persona Comparison

| Attribute | Sarah (Admin) | Marcus (Clinical) | Emily (Analyst) |
|-----------|---------------|-------------------|-----------------|
| **Primary Goal** | Operational overview | Real-time patient flow | Deep data analysis |
| **Usage Frequency** | 3-4 times daily | Continuous during shift | Daily, extended sessions |
| **Technical Skill** | Intermediate | Advanced | Expert |
| **Key Metric** | Cost per patient | Wait time | Predictive accuracy |
| **Device** | Desktop + iPad | Mobile-first | Desktop only |
| **Feature Priority** | Simplicity, alerts | Real-time, mobile | Customization, API |

---

> [!TIP]
> **Design Implication**: The dashboard should support **3 distinct interaction modes**:
> - **Executive View** (Sarah): High-level KPIs, visual cards, one-click exports
> - **Operational View** (Marcus): Real-time updates, drill-downs, mobile-responsive
> - **Analytical View** (Emily): Advanced filters, raw data access, export options
